# How to add a repo to Git From VSCode using CLI (Command Line Interface)
1.Check where you are
check your folder:
pwd
ls -a

2.Initialize the repo
Run this inside "Your folder":
git init

3.Add your files
git add .

4. Commit
git commit -m "Initial commit"

5. Connect to GitHub
Go to GitHub, create an empty repo named (whatever you want), without adding a README or .gitignore.
Then link your local folder to it:
git remote add origin https://github.com/USERNAME/REPO.git
Replace USERNAME and REPO.

6. Push
git push -u origin main

If your branch isnâ€™t named main, check with:
git branch
